DAMATURU – In an effort to ensure the proper and peaceful use of motorcycles in the Yobe North senatorial district, the Yobe State Road Traffic Management Agency (YOROTA) has today sensitized the users in Gashua town, the headquarters of Bade Local Government Area. The General Manager, YOROTA Babagana Alhaji Modu, led the advocacy team. He lectured on the modus operadi of the usage of the motorcycles for safety as well as the importance of profiling to enable smooth take up in the areas recently the Government lifted the ban. Court Declares Deductions From Federation Account For Police… 2022: Bisi Kolawole Wins Ekiti PDP Guber Primary Responding, the Chairman of Bade Local Government Council, Sanda Karabade, commended YOROTA operations in the state which according to him has greatly maintained strict compliance to traffic rules and regulations “this is reducing road crashes on our roads”. The Chairman further disclosed that they have come up with a law restricting the carriage of slaughtered animals on motorcycles in the area which according to him will go a long way in reducing the theft of livestock, slaughtered and conveyed on motorcycles. The YOROTA advocacy team was also at Jakusko Local Government Area where the Council Secretary, Usman Ahmed Dori received them on behalf of the Chairman and pledged their support to the agency in ensuring full compliance to all traffic rules and regulations along with ensuring registration of the users. “The registration will ensure crime-free society because details of the users will be captured”.